theorem
(x in L iff ( dist (x,L) ) = ( 0 ))
proof
thus (x in L implies ( dist (x,L) ) = ( 0 ))
proof
A1: (for r being  real number holds (r in ( dist_v (x,L) ) implies ( 0 ) <= r))
proof
let r being  real number;
assume r in ( dist_v (x,L) );
then (ex x0 being (Element of ( REAL n )) st (r = |. ( x - x0 ) .| & x0 in L));
hence thesis;
end;
A2: ( dist_v (x,L) ) is  bounded_below
proof
take ( 0 );
let r being  ext-real number;
assume r in ( dist_v (x,L) );
then (ex x0 being (Element of ( REAL n )) st (r = |. ( x - x0 ) .| & x0 in L));
hence thesis;
end;
assume A3: x in L;
|. ( x - x ) .| = |. ( 0* n ) .| by CKB10:1
.= ( sqrt |( ( 0* n ),( 0* n ) )| ) by EUCLID_4:15
.= ( 0 ) by EUCLID_4:17,SQUARE_1:17;
then A4: ( 0 ) in ( dist_v (x,L) ) by A3;
then (for s being  real number holds (( 0 ) < s implies (ex r being  real number st (r in ( dist_v (x,L) ) & r < ( ( 0 ) + s )))));
hence thesis by A4,A1,A2,SEQ_4:def 2;
end;

now
consider x0 being (Element of ( REAL n )) such that A5: x0 in L and A6: |. ( x - x0 ) .| = ( dist (x,L) ) by CKB70:1;
assume ( dist (x,L) ) = ( 0 );
then |( ( x - x0 ),( x - x0 ) )| = ( 0 ) by A6,EUCLID_4:16;
then ( x - x0 ) = ( 0* n ) by EUCLID_4:17;
hence x in L by A5,CKB10:1;
end;
hence thesis;
end;
